'''Gaff''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Kobok/Legends|Kobok]] living on [[Roon/Legends|Roon]] during the early days of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. He was the aide-de-camp to Governor [[Bisad Koong|Koong]] of the [[Tawntoom]] province. Gaff was a [[Color/Legends|yellow]]-skinned [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] with three orange compound [[Eye/Legends|eyes]]&mdash;the third was located in the back of his head.

==Biography==
A [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Kobok/Legends|Kobok]] from [[Roon/Legends|Roon]], Gaff left his [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] to make a name for himself in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] criminal underworld. Like all members of his [[Species/Legends|species]], Gaff had stingers on his [[Limb/Legends|arms]] that secreted a potent [[Poison/Legends|poison]], able to knock humanoids unconscious, though Koboks were also susceptible to their own poison. Over [[Time/Legends|time]], he honed his skills as a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]], [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]], and [[Spy/Legends|spy]]. He often wore a [[Koboth Insurgent Mantle]], although it was not known if Gaff actually participated in the [[Mavvan Conflict]], a brief war involving his species and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Gaff eventually returned to Roon, where he allied himself with [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Bisad Koong|Koong]]&mdash;a low point in his career, by his own estimation.

Koong dragged Gaff into a number of schemes to curry favor with [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Terrinald Screed/Legends|Terrinald Screed]], though none went according to plan. Eventually, Koong tried to kill Screed for betraying him, and destroyed the Tawntoom Citadel, with Gaff inside. Luckily, the Kobok survived the blast.<ref name="GatORW">''[[Geonosis and the Outer Rim Worlds]]''</ref>

